==English==

===Noun===
'''graffito''' (plural: '''[[graffiti]]''')

# (''archaeology and related fields'') An informal [[inscription]], as by a worker or vandal.
# (''rare'') A single instance of [[graffiti]] in the art/vandalism sense.

===Usage note===
The word ''graffito'' in the second meaning is not an accepted English word, but rather a back-formation used only by those who know the Latin singular form.

